deviceName.name: deviceName
deviceName.description: A textual description on the entity managed by the resident agent. It is mandatory that this only con- tain printable ASCII characters.

deviceIPAddress.name: deviceIPAddress
deviceIPAddress.description: The Network address, in this case the IP address, of the device. This object is required for use by the Local Management Interface.

deviceTime.name: deviceTime
deviceTime.description: The current time of day, in 24 hour format, as measured by the device. The representation shall use the standard HHMMSS format.

deviceDate.name: deviceDate
deviceDate.description: The current date, as measured by the device. The representation shall use the standard MMDDYYYY format.

fnbTRTable.name: fnbTRTable
fnbTRTable.description: A list of entries that provide connection status of Token Ring subsystems, for the FNB.

fnbTREntry.name: fnbTREntry
fnbTREntry.description: An entry in the fnbTRTable containing objects that provide FNB connection status for a Token Ring sub- system.

fnbTRIndex.name: fnbTRIndex
fnbTRIndex.description: An unique value for each Token Ring subsystem. Its value ranges between 1 and chassisSlots. The value for each interface must remain constant, at least, from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

fnbConnectLeft.name: fnbConnectLeft
fnbConnectLeft.description: The Connected Left board (board n + 1) has the following states: Detached == 1 (Management (only management) detached, read/write). Attached == 2 (Management/AutoMode attached, read/write). Faulted == 3 (Management/AutoMode tried to attach but failed READ ONLY).

fnbConnectRight.name: fnbConnectRight
fnbConnectRight.description: The Connected Right board (board n - 1) has the following states: Detached == 1 (Management (only management) detached, read/write). Attached == 2 (Management/AutoMode attached, read/write ). Faulted == 3 (Management/AutoMode tried to attach but failed, READ ONLY).

fnbBypass.name: fnbBypass
fnbBypass.description: Denotes the bypass status of the current Token Ring board. Bypassed means the board is NOT attached to the FNB.

fnbRPBypass.name: fnbRPBypass
fnbRPBypass.description: Denotes the Ring Port bypass status of the current Token Ring board. If this capability is not available on this board, the value 'other' is returned when read, and BADSETINFO when written.

fnbCSMACDTable.name: fnbCSMACDTable
fnbCSMACDTable.description: A list of entries that provide connection status of CSMA/CD subsystems, for the FNB.

fnbCSMACDEntry.name: fnbCSMACDEntry
fnbCSMACDEntry.description: An entry in the fnbCSMACDTable containing objects that provide FNB connection status for a CSMA/CD subsystem.

fnbCSMACDIndex.name: fnbCSMACDIndex
fnbCSMACDIndex.description: An unique value for each CSMACD subsystem. Its value ranges between 1 and chassisSlots. The value for each interface must remain constant, at least, from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

fnbConnect.name: fnbConnect
fnbConnect.description: Denotes the connection status of the CSMA/CD board to the inter-RIC bus.

fnbPortChanges.name: fnbPortChanges
fnbPortChanges.description: Denotes the number of times any port on the given MIM has changed it's connection to the inter-RIC bus.

fnbPortConnectTable.name: fnbPortConnectTable
fnbPortConnectTable.description: This table is used to control port association on ethernet devices. Only those boards that support port switching will be listed in this table.

fnbPortConnectEntry.name: fnbPortConnectEntry
fnbPortConnectEntry.description: Describes a specific port connection entry.

fnbPortConnectBoardIndex.name: fnbPortConnectBoardIndex
fnbPortConnectBoardIndex.description: An instance of a board for which this port assignment relationship exists.

fnbPortConnectPortIndex.name: fnbPortConnectPortIndex
fnbPortConnectPortIndex.description: An instance of a port for which this assignment relationship exists.

fnbPortConnectPortAssignment.name: fnbPortConnectPortAssignment
fnbPortConnectPortAssignment.description: The specific channel that the port is assigned.

fnbPortConnectCompID.name: fnbPortConnectCompID
fnbPortConnectCompID.description: This is the component ID as defined in the chassis MIB that this port is associated with. These components will be repeater components.

fnbPortConnectionChanges.name: fnbPortConnectionChanges
fnbPortConnectionChanges.description: Maintains the number of times any port within the mangement domain of this MIM changes it's port assignment.

chassisHWRev.name: chassisHWRev
chassisHWRev.description: Define the hardware revision of the device or sys- tem chassis.

chassisSlots.name: chassisSlots
chassisSlots.description: Denotes the number of available chassis slots.

chassisFNB.name: chassisFNB
chassisFNB.description: Denotes the presence or absence of the FNB.

chassisAlarmEna.name: chassisAlarmEna
chassisAlarmEna.description: Allow an audible alarm to be either enabled or dis- abled.

chassisAlarmState.name: chassisAlarmState
chassisAlarmState.description: Denotes the current condition of the power supply fault detection circuit. Setting a value of chassisNoFaultCondition(1) disables the current chassis alarm condition, and stops the current audible alarm from sounding. Setting a value of chassisFaultCondition(2) is not allowed. This object will read with the value of chassisNoFaultCondition(1) when the chassis is currently operating with no power faults detected. This object will read with the value of chassisFaultCondition(2) when the chassis is currently in a power fault condition.

powerTable.name: powerTable
powerTable.description: A list of power supply entries.

powerEntry.name: powerEntry
powerEntry.description: An entry in the powerTable providing objects for a power supply.

powerSupplyNum.name: powerSupplyNum
powerSupplyNum.description: Denotes the power supply that may have failed.

powerSupplyId.name: powerSupplyId
powerSupplyId.description: Identifies the type of power supply. For example, this could be used to identify power supplies which support additional remote management capabilities.

powerSupplyRedun.name: powerSupplyRedun
powerSupplyRedun.description: Identifies whether power redundancy is available within the chassis. Devices that do not support power supply redundancy, will return infoNotAvailable.

powerSupplyRemoteDisable.name: powerSupplyRemoteDisable
powerSupplyRemoteDisable.description: Provides Enable/Disable control of the power supply. For devices that do not support this capability, a set attempt will return BADVALUE, and a read will always return infoNotAvailable.

nB55HWAddress.name: nB55HWAddress
nB55HWAddress.reference: This value is the same as ifPhysAddress in RFC 1213.

nB55HWRev.name: nB55HWRev
nB55HWRev.description: Denotes the revision of the nB55 board. A value of one denotes Revision 1, a value of two denotes Revi- sion 2, and so on.

nB55FWRev.name: nB55FWRev
nB55FWRev.description: Denotes the revision of firmware in the module. The first octets provides the version, and the second provides the revision.

mRXIHWAddress.name: mRXIHWAddress
mRXIHWAddress.reference: This value is the same as ifPhysAddress in RFC 1213.

mRXIHWRev.name: mRXIHWRev
mRXIHWRev.description: Denotes the revision of the mRXI board. A value of one denotes Revision 1, a value of two denotes Revi- sion 2, and so on.

mRXIFWRev.name: mRXIFWRev
mRXIFWRev.description: Denotes the revision of firmware in the module. The first octets provides the version, and the second provides the revision.

iRM3HWAddress.name: iRM3HWAddress
iRM3HWAddress.reference: This value is the same as ifPhysAddress in RFC 1213.

iRM3HWRev.name: iRM3HWRev
iRM3HWRev.description: Denotes the revision of the IRM3 board. A value of one denotes Revision 1, a value of two denotes Revi- sion 2, and so on.

iRM3FWRev.name: iRM3FWRev
iRM3FWRev.description: Denotes the revision of firmware in the module. The first octets provides the version, and the second provides the revision.

iRM3PortAssoc.name: iRM3PortAssoc
iRM3PortAssoc.description: Controls how front panel ports are associated with the Irm3.

iRM3BPSupport.name: iRM3BPSupport
iRM3BPSupport.description: Denotes whether or not Backplane Protocol Support is present in the current version of the IRM3.

tRMMHWAddress.name: tRMMHWAddress
tRMMHWAddress.reference: This value is the same as ifPhysAddress in RFC 1213.

tRMMHWRev.name: tRMMHWRev
tRMMHWRev.description: Denotes the revision of the tRMM board. A value of one denotes Revision 1, a value of two denotes Revi- sion 2, and so on.

tRMMFWRev.name: tRMMFWRev
tRMMFWRev.description: Denotes the revision of firmware in the module. The first octets provides the version, and the second provides the revision.

eMMEHWAddress.name: eMMEHWAddress
eMMEHWAddress.reference: This value is the same as ifPhysAddress in RFC 1213.

eMMEHWRev.name: eMMEHWRev
eMMEHWRev.description: Denotes the revision of the eMME board. A value of one denotes Revision 1, a value of two denotes Revi- sion 2, and so on.

eMMEFWRev.name: eMMEFWRev
eMMEFWRev.description: Denotes the revision of firmware in the module. The first octets provides the version, and the second provides the revision.

eMMEBoardMap.name: eMMEBoardMap
eMMEBoardMap.description: Denotes a bit encoded representation of the slots that contain MIM boards. If a bit is a one then the board is present.

fPRedundReset.name: fPRedundReset
fPRedundReset.description: If this object is set to Reset it will cause a reset of the front panel redundancy. Setting this object to NoReset will do nothing. This object will always be read as NoReset.

fPRedundPollInterval.name: fPRedundPollInterval
fPRedundPollInterval.description: Get/Set the number of seconds between polls for front panel redundancy.

fPRedundRetrys.name: fPRedundRetrys
fPRedundRetrys.description: Get/Set the the number of unanswered polls allowed for the front panel redundancy before it switches ports.

fPRedundNumAddr.name: fPRedundNumAddr
fPRedundNumAddr.description: Get the number of IP Addresses associated with front panel redundancy.

fPRedundAddAddr.name: fPRedundAddAddr
fPRedundAddAddr.description: Add an IP Address to the polling list for the front panel redundancy.

fPRedundDelAddr.name: fPRedundDelAddr
fPRedundDelAddr.description: Delete an IP Address from the polling list for the front panel redundancy.

fPRedundActivePort.name: fPRedundActivePort
fPRedundActivePort.description: Get/Set the front panel port you want to be active when front panel redundancy is enabled.

fPRedundEnable.name: fPRedundEnable
fPRedundEnable.description: If this object is set to enable, the front panel redundancy will be activated. If this object is set to disable, the front panel redundancy will be deactivated. When read, this object will returns the state of the object based on the last request made.

fPRedundAddrTable.name: fPRedundAddrTable
fPRedundAddrTable.description: A list of entries that provide IP address information for front panel redundancy.

fPRedundAddrEntry.name: fPRedundAddrEntry
fPRedundAddrEntry.description: An entry in the fPRedundAddrTable providing objects for front panel redundancy.

fPRedundAddrId.name: fPRedundAddrId
fPRedundAddrId.description: A unique value identifying an element in a sequence of member IP Addresses which belong to the front panel redundancy. This value goes from 1 to the maximum number of IP Addresses which may be included in front panel redundancy.

fPRedundAddrIPAddr.name: fPRedundAddrIPAddr
fPRedundAddrIPAddr.description: Returns an IP Address associated with the front panel redundancy.

upsID.name: upsID
upsID.description: Denotes a type code which refers to the manufactur- ers and model of the UPS.

upsUpTime.name: upsUpTime
upsUpTime.description: Denotes the operating time, in hours, since the UPS was last powered on.

upsDisable.name: upsDisable
upsDisable.description: Allows the UPS to be disabled. A set turns of the UPS for those systems, so equipped. A get/get-next always returns 0.

upsDisconnect.name: upsDisconnect
upsDisconnect.description: Allows the UPS backup power system to conserve its battery. Setting the object to a value of 1 turns off the power system. A get/get-next always retuns a 0.

upsTest.name: upsTest
upsTest.description: Denotes the status performed on the UPS. A write unitOK(1) intiates the test. A read indicates status of test.

upsBatteryCapacity.name: upsBatteryCapacity
upsBatteryCapacity.description: Denotes the percentage of battery capacity left, 100% being a fully-charged battery.

upsACLineVoltsIn.name: upsACLineVoltsIn
upsACLineVoltsIn.description: Denotes the input AC utility line voltage.

dlForceOnBoot.name: dlForceOnBoot
dlForceOnBoot.description: When set to a 1, the system will request a download, during the next system restart. If no server is found and the current image in flash memory is valid, the system will boot using the flash-resident image.

dlCommitRAMToFlash.name: dlCommitRAMToFlash
dlCommitRAMToFlash.description: When written with a 1, the boot software will erase flash memory, compress the downloaded code, and save the compressed image into flash memory. Upon com- pletion of this operation, the flash memory driver resets this object to 0, indicating completion of the programming operation.

dlInitiateColdBoot.name: dlInitiateColdBoot
dlInitiateColdBoot.description: When written with a 1, the boot software intiates a system reboot. All MIB variables used to control the exact nature of the download should be set, prior to activating a system reset. A read always returns a 0.

dlTFTPRequestHost.name: dlTFTPRequestHost
dlTFTPRequestHost.description: The IP address of the server to be used, when firmware is to be loaded across the network.

dlTFTPRequest.name: dlTFTPRequest
dlTFTPRequest.description: The filename requested of the server, when firmware is to be loaded across the network.

dlLastImageFilename.name: dlLastImageFilename
dlLastImageFilename.description: Filename of the last image to be successfully loaded into memory.

dlLastServerIPAddress.name: dlLastServerIPAddress
dlLastServerIPAddress.description: The IP address of the server used to load the present image in flash memory.

dlFlashSize.name: dlFlashSize
dlFlashSize.description: Denotes the size, in bytes, of flash memory con- tained on this module.

dlFlashCount.name: dlFlashCount
dlFlashCount.description: Denotes the number of times that flash memory has been reprogrammed. This value is initialzed to 1, when the module is initially powered up.

dlFirmwareBase.name: dlFirmwareBase
dlFirmwareBase.description: Denotes the starting address of the firmware in RAM.

dlFirmwareTop.name: dlFirmwareTop
dlFirmwareTop.description: Denotes the ending address of firmware in RAM.

dlFirmwareStart.name: dlFirmwareStart
dlFirmwareStart.description: Denotes the start address of the firmware, in RAM, as established by the boot process.

dlBootRev.name: dlBootRev
dlBootRev.description: Denotes the revision of boot firmware in the module. The first octets provides the version, and the second provides the revision.

dlForceBootp.name: dlForceBootp
dlForceBootp.description: When set, this variable forces the client to send a BOOTP request packet when rebooting. The client will make several attempts before timing out if a server does not respond. This variable stays set. When set to a 1 it should always be read as a one. When set to zero it should always be read as zero.

dlServerName.name: dlServerName
dlServerName.description: This OID is reserved for future use of the Bootp server name. This field can be used when a client wants to get boot information from a particular bootp server.

dlOnLineDownLoad.name: dlOnLineDownLoad
dlOnLineDownLoad.description: During normal operation this object has the value of 1. By setting this object to a value of forceDownLoad(2) an online download will be performed. By setting this object to a value of forceDownLoadReset(3) an online down load will be performed and a reset will be forced upon successful completion of the download.

dlOperStatus.name: dlOperStatus
dlOperStatus.description: This object reflects the status of the download code. A value of normalOperation(3) reflects either a down load was started but has finished normally and no reset was specified or no down load has been started. A value of downLoadActive only appears while a down load is in progress. A value of downLoadCompleteError reflects that a down load was started however an error was detected.

dlNetAddress.name: dlNetAddress
dlNetAddress.description: IP Address of the server to be used when an image is to be downloaded using the Runtime TFTP Download.

dlFileName.name: dlFileName
dlFileName.description: Filename requested of the server when an image is to be downloaded using the Runtime TFTP Download. This should be a complete path filename.

dlErrorString.name: dlErrorString
dlErrorString.description: If the value of ctDLOperStatus is downloadCompleteError(5) then this object will provide a more complete description of the error. Otherwise this object will be the zero length string.

dlTftpServerGatewayIPAddress.name: dlTftpServerGatewayIPAddress
dlTftpServerGatewayIPAddress.description: The IP address of the gateway/router which connects this SNMP agent to the TFTP server.
